node.text:
Ducks Talulah Beisel and Kyle Trefny are among the thousands of wildland firefighters battling blazes across the West this summer.
Talulah is a fourth-year student majoring in human physiology and minoring in music, and Kyle is a second-year majoring in economics and minoring in environmental studies.

"This is our first year on fires," Kyle said. "We’re on a hand crew, putting out active areas, setting back-burns and helping residents make their homes resilient. I’ve worked in the Ochoco National Forest in Oregon and spent most of the summer on the Divide Complex fires in Montana, where I got to work with Talulah!" 

Said Talulah: “I really wanted to work in an outdoor setting while doing something productive for the environment.”

We are very grateful for Kyle, Talulah and all of the firefighters who are on the frontlines protecting our communities and keeping us safe.
